/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/runtime/results/codex-patlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-step-001-receptionist.md:16:   The local record does not support “single Fourier mode” as the right support notion for this branch. It explicitly keeps the support question open among single modes, conjugate-complete pairs, and packet-level objects, but the rest of the corpus leans toward packet-level/helical packet language as the real mission object ([CHAIN.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/CHAIN.md#L82), [MISSION.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/atlas-source/atlas-exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit-MISSION.md#L75), [planner.md](/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-philosopher-atlas/missions/exact-ns-no-near-closed-tao-circuit/planning-runs/run-001/planner.md#L13)).  
