+- Decision `012` explicitly marks the old branch `invalidated`, not active.
+  Run `003` should therefore use the Step-8 negative as new evidence, not
+  silently reopen the failed dynamic-audit chain.
+- `F_SL(1/16)` remains the carried friendly witness for repaired `G_tmpl`;
+  `F_DT(delta, eta)` remains the hostile comparator;
+  `F_SS(1/12)` now matters primarily as a **separation witness** between static
+  admissibility and honest exact closure.
+
+## Portfolio Summary
+
+### Chain 01 - Exact `F_SL(rho)` Template Frontier
+
+Central premise: the cleanest surviving theorem-facing positive route is now
+family-local.
+ Freeze repaired `G_tmpl` on the carried scale-separated family `F_SL(rho)`,
+ derive the exact `rho`-dependent defect ledger, and determine the true
+ admissible interval and sharp boundary.
+
+### Chain 02 - Admissibility Versus Exact-Closure Separation
+
+Central premise: Step `008` may have revealed the real obstruction object.
+ Use `F_SS(1/12)` to test, on the frozen one-bridge ledger, whether passing
+ repaired `G_tmpl` and/or repaired `G_leak` actually implies any honest
+ finite-closure statement, or whether exact closure is a genuinely separate
+ requirement.
+
+### Chain 03 - Support-Level One-Bridge No-Finite-Closure Theorem
+
+Central premise: the highest-upside obstruction route is to repair the precise
+ gap Step `008` exposed.
+ Freeze an explicit wavevector/helicity realization class for the one-bridge
+ packet, enumerate all forced triads, and try to prove that no realization of
+ the Tao-like five-channel core closes finitely without extra support or
+ truncation.
+
+### Chain 04 - Adversarial Exact Near-Circuit Construction Beyond `F_SS`
+
+Central premise: the firewall idea is not saved by killing one witness.
+ Search for a **new** explicit exact support family, broader than the frozen
+ `F_SS(1/12)` packet but still finite and canonical, that can satisfy repaired
+ `G_tmpl`, repaired `G_leak`, and honest finite closure simultaneously.
+
+## Major Differences Between Chains
+
+- Chain `01` is family-local and theorem-facing.
+  It works inside the already carried positive family `F_SL(rho)` and asks for
+  an exact repaired-template frontier, not a new closure object or a support
+  search.
+- Chain `02` is relation-facing.
+  It studies the implication gap between the Step-6 promoted gates and honest
+  exact closure on the frozen ledger.
+- Chain `03` is support-level and obstruction-facing.
+  It tries to turn the Step-8 witness-local failure into a theorem-shaped
+  impossibility or forced-support lower bound.
+- Chain `04` is constructive and adversarial.
+  It looks for an explicit exact survivor outside the invalidated `F_SS`
+  branch, not a proof first.
+
+## Portfolio Discipline
+
+- Start from the Step-6, Step-7, and Step-8 canonical results.
+  Do not reopen broad definition work from run `001` unless a chain hits its
+  own named kill condition.
+- Treat `F_SS(1/12)` as a closed branch for dynamic-audit purposes.
+  Reuse it only as a separation witness, a calibration point, or an explicit
+  support-level test case.
+- Keep classwise admissibility and support-level exact closure distinct unless a
+  chain explicitly proves an implication between them.
+- Keep the same packet semantics, role order, spectator partition, fixed window
+  `I = [0, 1]`, and repaired Step-6 thresholds unless a chain's whole purpose
+  is to define and justify one new closure-level object on the same ledger.
+- Preserve one genuine moonshot in the top portfolio.
+  This mission still needs either a theorem-shaped impossibility or an explicit
+  exact near-circuit challenger, not only a cleaner audit memo.
+
+## Suggested Priority
+
+- First priority: Chain `02`.
+  It uses the new Step-8 evidence most directly, has the best presentable floor
+  after the replan, and can decide whether the promoted Step-6 gates are still
+  theorem-grade mission objects or only screening tools.
+- Second priority: Chain `03`.
+  It has the highest obstruction-side ceiling because it could turn the current
+  support-level gap into a real impossibility theorem or forced-extra-support
+  lower bound.
+- Third priority: Chain `01`.
+  It is the cleanest surviving positive-family theorem route and helps prevent
+  the obstruction story from overclaiming beyond what the carried `F_SL` family
+  really earns.
+- Keep Chain `04` active despite its lower floor.
+  It has the highest counterexample upside because it is the only branch that
+  can still kill the firewall idea with a fresh explicit exact construction.

